<div class="xar-mod-head">
    <span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Keywords Administration</xar:mlstring></span>
        </div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin_generic.gif', 'base')#" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" class="xar-module-icon" />
    <h2>
        <xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring>
    </h2>
    <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
    </h3>
        <p><em><xar:mlstring>Keywords is a Xaraya Utility Module.</xar:mlstring></em>
        <xar:mlstring>that allows you to assign keywords to module items (taxonomy) and to look up items by keyword. Enable its hooks for any module where you want to use it...</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
       </h3>
         <p><xar:mlstring>After enabling the keywords hooks for a particular module, you'll see an input box where you can fill in relevant keywords whenever you create or modify a module item.
         Afterwards, when viewing an item, you can retrieve a list of other items having the same keyword(s).</xar:mlstring></p>
         <p><xar:mlstring>This module, now, may also restrict keywords to a predefined set of words, tipical for each hooked module.</xar:mlstring>
         </p>
         <p><xar:mlstring>In the future thi module may try to extract keywords
         automatically from other fields on create/update. Contributions in that or other directions are welcome :-)</xar:mlstring></p>
         <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
           <p>
           <xar:mlstring>There are no included blocks at this time</xar:mlstring>
           </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
    </h3>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>new/create/modify/update/delete -- Allows you to create/update keywords</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>display/search -- Allows you to display/search keywords</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-foot xar-align-center xar-padding-thick">
    <p>
        <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found here. [modules module]</xar:mlstring>
    </p>
</div>
